body.name: SEDETA Lift Top Coffee Table, 4 in 1 Multi-Function Convertible Coffee Tables with Storage and Hidden Compartment, Farmhouse Coffee Table Converts to Dining Table for Living Room, Grey
features: 【4-in-1 Lift Design】Unique lift top coffee table design to meet more needs--when fully unfolded, it becomes a dining or gaming coffee table for 8 people; when half expanded, it becomes a workstation for 2 people to use at the same time without disturbing each other; when lifting top is closed, farmhouse coffee table is suitable for storing sundries.

【Chic Farmhouse Style】Size: 39.3"W × 19.7"D× 25.8"H. This 4 in 1 Multi-Function coffee table garners attention with its sliding barn doors and farmhouse style. Its two-tone distressed oak finish delivers a naturally aged feel and creates a cozy and retro vibe. This coffee table is perfect for any rustic, cottage, shabby chic, or casual space.

【Large Storage Spaces】Beneath the handy lift-top surface are 3 hidden storage areas that provide you with the perfect spot to stow away any around-home essentials you typically wouldn't want your guests to see. The lower open storage shlef & 2 sliding barn doors can be placed laptop, chess, remote controllers or knick-knack. Keep your living space tidy and organized with this unique feature.

【Quality upgrade】The double-top lift adopts a more sturdy and special lifting metal arm, which is more load-bearing than ordinary coffee table with lift top. The thickened 4 support legs with 1.8'' X 1.8'' can hold up to 150 pounds and can easily accommodate your items with no problems, with 100% No Wobble.

【Easy Assemble & After-sales Service】To make assembling this sturdy lift top coffee table as effortless as possible, we have included clear and detailed instructions, numbered parts. If your item arrives damaged, scratched or missing part, please feel free to contact us, we will send you free replacement or offer a partial refund.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to assemble, Pretty coffee table
reviews.reviewText: I like the wooden feel of all the pieces The instructions were well laid out and very easy to follow. It does everything it's suppose to do. It goes from a coffee table with a computer stand to a dining table which can seat four. Plus this coffee table offers multiple storage areas. Great for doing any arts and craft; especially for myself doing Diamond Art. I would recommend this table to family and friends.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice Multi-Functional Convertible Coffee Table
reviews.reviewText: I really like the look and the functionality of this coffee table. The color/pattern fit in to our existing decor perfectly... it definitely met my expectation. However, the assembly instruction was not as clear as it should have been. The entire kit has MANY components... It took my husband a few hours to assemble it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars We love card night!
reviews.reviewText: I love this table! I’m not a coffee table person but when I saw all the little tables that pop out I had to get it. My daughter uses the baby one for her tablet and it keeps her from looking down and straining her neck. The fold out table is perfect for a 4 person card game and you could easily double up and make it up to 8 people! Then it easily folds up and you can’t even tell. There’s also an inside shelf for electronics or movies and two sliding barn doors that cover two more shelving systems on each side. It was easy to assemble other than figuring out our left and right sides when installing the smaller tables opposite from each other, make sure to read the directions! And you can’t beat the price!!

reviews.reviewText: This was fairly easy to put together. I did it by myself but, it took me 2 hours.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Overall nice, sturdy piece, BUT...
reviews.reviewText: We put this table in our playroom in front of our U-shaped sectional. Worked out great. Just a heads up before you purchase:1. Unit is not as "GREY" as it appears in the listing pics. Definitely has more brownish tones mixed in. Wished it was more grey like the pics. (Minus 1 star)2. There is a thin panel that slides inside a channel. The two side assemblies also have the channel to trap it place once its all screwed together. The problem is that the factory routered channel was gone over a 2nd time (about 3/4" to each end of the channel was added), because the channel wasn't long enough for the panel board to fit into it. One of the side assemblies had been fixed, but the other side had not. So you can extend the channel with about a 3/16" rabbit bit on a router, or notch out the corners of the panel board, which is what I did. (Minus a 2nd star)3. I'm very handy and have lots of tools. But it still took me 3+ hours to assemble.4. Do not let kids play with this! Don't get me wrong, it's very sturdy - IF - yes, IF you follow the directions on how to use the pop-up sections of the table. If you forget to raise the small platform up, before unfolding the 2nd half of the table top, the hinges will get ripped off. So pay attention and handle with care.5. The packaging was great 👍6. The finish of the table seems to be pretty resilient, so should last a long time.So if you're OK with #s 1-4, buy one and you won't regret it! Nice table overall 👌
